@startuml secuencia-rate-limiting
!theme plain
title Experimento 04 - Diagrama de Secuencia: Rate Limiting por Configuracion

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #FDEDEC
skinparam participantBorderColor #E74C3C

actor "Cliente\n(normal)" as C
actor "Cliente\n(alta carga)" as CH
participant "Nginx Ingress\nController" as NGINX
participant "limit_req_zone\n(Counter por IP)" as ZONE
participant "api-service\n:8080" as API
participant "auth-service\n:8080" as AUTH
database "PostgreSQL\n:5432" as PG

== Flujo Baseline (Sin Rate Limiting) ==

note over C, PG : **Baseline**: Sin anotaciones de limite, RATE_LIMIT_ENABLED=false
C -> NGINX : HTTPS GET /profile
NGINX -> API : HTTP (sin evaluar zona)
API -> AUTH : POST /validate
AUTH -> PG : SELECT usuario
PG --> AUTH : user record
AUTH --> API : JWT valido
API --> NGINX : HTTP 200
NGINX --> C : HTTPS 200

CH -> NGINX : 5000 req/min (alta carga)
NGINX -> API : todos los requests procesados
note over CH, API : Sin limite -> posible saturacion\ndel backend bajo alta carga

== Flujo Moderate (1200 rpm) ==

C -> NGINX : HTTPS GET /profile\n(Peticion #1 del cliente)
NGINX -> ZONE : Consultar contador para\nIP del cliente
ZONE -> ZONE : Contador actual: 800 rpm\n< 1200 rpm (bajo limite)
ZONE --> NGINX : PERMITIR
NGINX -> API : HTTP GET /profile
API -> AUTH : validar JWT
AUTH --> API : token OK
API --> NGINX : HTTP 200
NGINX --> C : HTTPS 200

CH -> NGINX : HTTPS GET /profile\n(Peticion #1500 del cliente)
NGINX -> ZONE : Consultar contador\nIP del cliente
ZONE -> ZONE : Contador actual: 1500 rpm\n> 1200 rpm (EXCEDE LIMITE)
ZONE --> NGINX : RECHAZAR
NGINX --> CH : HTTP 503 Service Unavailable
note over CH, ZONE : burst-multiplier=1: sin cola\nRechaze inmediato al exceder limite

== Flujo Strict (300 rpm) ==

C -> NGINX : HTTPS GET /profile\n(Peticion #50 del cliente)
NGINX -> ZONE : Consultar contador\nIP del cliente
ZONE -> ZONE : Contador actual: 250 rpm\n< 300 rpm (bajo limite)
ZONE --> NGINX : PERMITIR
NGINX -> API : HTTP GET /profile
API --> NGINX : HTTP 200
NGINX --> C : HTTPS 200

CH -> NGINX : HTTPS GET /profile\n(Peticion #400 del cliente)
NGINX -> ZONE : Consultar contador\nIP del cliente
ZONE -> ZONE : Contador actual: 400 rpm\n> 300 rpm (EXCEDE LIMITE)
ZONE --> NGINX : RECHAZAR
NGINX --> CH : HTTP 503 Service Unavailable
note over CH, ZONE : Strict: kicks in mucho antes\nque Moderate (300 vs 1200 rpm)\nMayor tasa de rechazo bajo carga normal

== Resumen Comparativo ==

note over C, PG
  **Baseline**: 0 HTTP 503, latencia minima, throughput maximo
  **Moderate (1200 rpm)**: HTTP 503 solo bajo alta carga (>20 rps)
  **Strict (300 rpm)**: HTTP 503 frecuente incluso bajo carga moderada (>5 rps)

  Variable medida: tasa de HTTP 503, latencia p50/p95/p99, throughput
  Herramienta: k6 con 50% GET /profile, 30% GET /users, 20% POST /users
end note

@enduml
